THE PIECE PROJECT"
-------------------------
I came to the U.S. because I had a dream. A dream to create films to make people think and feel, and maybe even inspire someone to get up and do something.  After 9/11, my dad lost his job in Canada so we moved overseas to Dubai, U.A.E. where I glimpsed nearly every culture imaginable. It truly was a melting pot. I grew up around people of every race, color, ethnicity, nationality, sexuality and religion.  I was taught that you cannot assume anything based on how someone looks, is dressed, or which God(s) they worship but how they treat people.  I went to high school where there were still jocks, nerds and drama geeks but nobody was made fun of because of who they were taught to pray to.  My dream to make films that make people think, feel and move has felt more and more relevant. Except now the name of the game isn't my six year old self's dream of following Angelina Jolie in her work with the U.N. ... It's about reminding each other how to treat people. With compassion. With consideration. To look someone in the eye, shake their hand, and speak to them before you make an assumption of who they are. 
We are all a piece of the fabric that makes up America. No matter race, gender, sexuality, or origin, we have all shaped our country. And by coming together, we can all make a difference. Where do you fit into the puzzle?
